full_text: RT @emmaxdaviess: TW // sexual assault //                       I‚Äôve never really spoken at length about my experiences with sexual assault‚Ä¶
full_text(utf-8): b'RT @emmaxdaviess: TW // sexual assault //                       I\xe2\x80\x99ve never really spoken at length about my experiences with sexual assault\xe2\x80\xa6'

full_text: I‚Äôm so angry men do this. That they live in a world where they face no shame or consequences for their behaviour. The woman takes the guilt and shame. I‚Äôm still embarrassed, but I wanted to talk about my experiences. Fin. (17/17)
full_text(utf-8): b'I\xe2\x80\x99m so angry men do this. That they live in a world where they face no shame or consequences for their behaviour. The woman takes the guilt and shame. I\xe2\x80\x99m still embarrassed, but I wanted to talk about my experiences. Fin. (17/17)'

full_text: I am terrified it‚Äôs going to happen again. For years I thought my experiences were not bad enough to share. I downplayed these incidents. But they are valid, and show how casual and widespread rape culture is, how entitled men feel to women‚Äôs bodies. (16/17)
full_text(utf-8): b'I am terrified it\xe2\x80\x99s going to happen again. For years I thought my experiences were not bad enough to share. I downplayed these incidents. But they are valid, and show how casual and widespread rape culture is, how entitled men feel to women\xe2\x80\x99s bodies. (16/17)'

full_text: I blamed myself for a lot of my experiences. But I want to make it clear - none of these things were my fault. I did not encourage them. I was a young girl. Grown men decided to sexually assault me.There are other instances I‚Äôve blocked out of my memories (15/?)
full_text(utf-8): b'I blamed myself for a lot of my experiences. But I want to make it clear - none of these things were my fault. I did not encourage them. I was a young girl. Grown men decided to sexually assault me.There are other instances I\xe2\x80\x99ve blocked out of my memories (15/?)'

full_text: The other devastating and troubling thing about this is that I can never tell my mum about it. I can never ask if he had had ever done those things to her. It‚Äôs hard being the only woman in the house. There‚Äôs a lack of understanding and empathy and shared experience. (14/?)
full_text(utf-8): b'The other devastating and troubling thing about this is that I can never tell my mum about it. I can never ask if he had had ever done those things to her. It\xe2\x80\x99s hard being the only woman in the house. There\xe2\x80\x99s a lack of understanding and empathy and shared experience. (14/?)'

full_text: I said no, and he left soon after that. I was terrified and trembling and in disbelief. I also hated myself for letting him into the house, for being so stupid. Whenever I see a post man, I am terrified that it‚Äôs him. (13/?)
full_text(utf-8): b'I said no, and he left soon after that. I was terrified and trembling and in disbelief. I also hated myself for letting him into the house, for being so stupid. Whenever I see a post man, I am terrified that it\xe2\x80\x99s him. (13/?)'

full_text: But as he was leaving, he hugged me again really tight. I just remember how constricted I felt, how scared I was that this was a strong grown man. He kissed both of my cheeks and my collarbone. He asked if he could kiss me on the lips and I said no. He asked again. (12/?)
full_text(utf-8): b'But as he was leaving, he hugged me again really tight. I just remember how constricted I felt, how scared I was that this was a strong grown man. He kissed both of my cheeks and my collarbone. He asked if he could kiss me on the lips and I said no. He asked again. (12/?)'

full_text: And rubbed on the top of my bum, and I managed to push him off. He didn‚Äôt behave like anything was wrong. He touched and held my head and hands, talking about how lovely my mum was and how sad it was that I had lost her. I managed to usher him towards the front door (11/?)
full_text(utf-8): b'And rubbed on the top of my bum, and I managed to push him off. He didn\xe2\x80\x99t behave like anything was wrong. He touched and held my head and hands, talking about how lovely my mum was and how sad it was that I had lost her. I managed to usher him towards the front door (11/?)'

full_text: And I wasn‚Äôt sure. Felt a bit uncomfortable. But he asked again and I said okay. He hugged me really tight, I didn‚Äôt hug him back. He started rubbing and massaging his hands over my back, leaning into my shoulder/collarbone with his face. His hands went lower (10/?)
full_text(utf-8): b'And I wasn\xe2\x80\x99t sure. Felt a bit uncomfortable. But he asked again and I said okay. He hugged me really tight, I didn\xe2\x80\x99t hug him back. He started rubbing and massaging his hands over my back, leaning into my shoulder/collarbone with his face. His hands went lower (10/?)'

full_text: And my mum was really lovely to everyone. I was the only person downstairs in the house, but I thought it would be okay. He came in and looked at some pictures of mum and chatted for a bit. He seemed really upset about her death. He asked me if he could hug me (9/?)
full_text(utf-8): b'And my mum was really lovely to everyone. I was the only person downstairs in the house, but I thought it would be okay. He came in and looked at some pictures of mum and chatted for a bit. He seemed really upset about her death. He asked me if he could hug me (9/?)'

full_text: And his first question was ‚ÄòWhat were you wearing?‚Äô. I never reported it. Aged 20, in September last year, my mum had died a few weeks before. Our post man (in his 40s) came to the door and asked if he could come in to see a picture of her. They had spoken a lot, (8/?)
full_text(utf-8): b'And his first question was \xe2\x80\x98What were you wearing?\xe2\x80\x99. I never reported it. Aged 20, in September last year, my mum had died a few weeks before. Our post man (in his 40s) came to the door and asked if he could come in to see a picture of her. They had spoken a lot, (8/?)'

full_text: Finally the bus terminated and I stood up, the man moved and I got off. I was trembling. I was so angry and scared and embarrassed and I hated myself that I hadn‚Äôt responded. I just let him touch me. Still makes me feel sick. Told my then boyfriend that evening, (7/?)
full_text(utf-8): b'Finally the bus terminated and I stood up, the man moved and I got off. I was trembling. I was so angry and scared and embarrassed and I hated myself that I hadn\xe2\x80\x99t responded. I just let him touch me. Still makes me feel sick. Told my then boyfriend that evening, (7/?)'

full_text: Kept rubbing his arm on my side. Rubbing his elbow into my ribs and stomach. It hurt. I shut down. I didn‚Äôt do anything. I just stared out the window, hoping he would stop. After a while, he started rubbing my leg, putting his hand under my leg, trying to lift my dress up. (6/?)
full_text(utf-8): b'Kept rubbing his arm on my side. Rubbing his elbow into my ribs and stomach. It hurt. I shut down. I didn\xe2\x80\x99t do anything. I just stared out the window, hoping he would stop. After a while, he started rubbing my leg, putting his hand under my leg, trying to lift my dress up. (6/?)'

full_text: Aged 17, I was on the bus home when a man sat next to me. It was a 50 min bus ride. He spent the entire ride getting closer and closer to me. Started rubbing his arm on my side. At first I thought I was really confused and thought it was accidental. But he kept going (5/?)
full_text(utf-8): b'Aged 17, I was on the bus home when a man sat next to me. It was a 50 min bus ride. He spent the entire ride getting closer and closer to me. Started rubbing his arm on my side. At first I thought I was really confused and thought it was accidental. But he kept going (5/?)'

full_text: I thought I deserved it because I was wearing a tank top. Aged 15, I was in a park near my house, and a man aged about 35 started talking to me. ‚ÄòDo you live near here?‚Äô ‚ÄòWhere are you from?‚Äô ‚ÄòHow old are you?‚Äô I was scared and left the park asap. (4/?)
full_text(utf-8): b'I thought I deserved it because I was wearing a tank top. Aged 15, I was in a park near my house, and a man aged about 35 started talking to me. \xe2\x80\x98Do you live near here?\xe2\x80\x99 \xe2\x80\x98Where are you from?\xe2\x80\x99 \xe2\x80\x98How old are you?\xe2\x80\x99 I was scared and left the park asap. (4/?)'

full_text: I had no idea how to respond so I flipped him off. This annoyed him. I started walking down the pavement but traffic was slow and the van crawled next to me, the man calling and gesturing at me the entire time. I was terrified. I don‚Äôt remember much. I never told anyone. (3/?)
full_text(utf-8): b'I had no idea how to respond so I flipped him off. This annoyed him. I started walking down the pavement but traffic was slow and the van crawled next to me, the man calling and gesturing at me the entire time. I was terrified. I don\xe2\x80\x99t remember much. I never told anyone. (3/?)'

full_text: When I was 14/15, I would get catcalled by men whilst I was walking on the pavement. I was simultaneously furious and terrified. One time I remember a man was staring at me from a van passenger seat and when I looked up and saw him, he made gestures imitating a handjob. (2/?)
full_text(utf-8): b'When I was 14/15, I would get catcalled by men whilst I was walking on the pavement. I was simultaneously furious and terrified. One time I remember a man was staring at me from a van passenger seat and when I looked up and saw him, he made gestures imitating a handjob. (2/?)'

full_text: ...'At least the British brought a system of government. We were invaded by the Dutch, and they didn't leave us shit.' The woman also said 'Women's opinions have always been ignored. If women had been listened to, perhaps these terrible things wouldn't have happened.' (6/?)

full_text: I recommended she read the whole book, to see how Lindqvist had reached a point where he could make such a summation. Yknow, how books work. She told me about an Indonesian man she met, who apparently said 'I wish we'd been invaded by the British'... (5/?)

full_text: The woman explained she disagreed, because that statement (from p. 160) was a generalisation of all Europeans, when the 'really bad stuff' was the actions of a 'few fucking psychos'. (4/?)
full_text(utf-8): b"The woman explained she disagreed, because that statement (from p. 160) was a generalisation of all Europeans, when the 'really bad stuff' was the actions of a 'few fucking psychos'. (4/?)"

full_text: She was confused, asked what he meant.Tried to explain as best I could, seeing as I had only just read the statement for the first time. Tried to sum up Lindqvist's argument that Hitler's anti-Semitism+previous European colonial genocides and racial science led to Holocaust (3/?)
